When NOT to Use an MSP
You might not need an MSP if:
	âˆ™	âœ… You have 5 or fewer users with simple needs (Google Workspace + laptop support)
	âˆ™	âœ… You have a competent part-time IT person who can handle everything
	âˆ™	âœ… Youâ€™re comfortable with business risk of no redundancy/backup for your IT person
	âˆ™	âœ… Your IT needs are purely software-as-a-service with no on-premise infrastructure
