	âˆ™	Your needs are truly intermittent (a few hours per quarter)
	âˆ™	You have technical leadership who can direct contractors
	âˆ™	You donâ€™t have mission-critical uptime requirements
Decision Framework
Shortlist 3-4 MSPs based on:
	1.	Similar client size/industry
	2.	Geographic proximity (for onsite needs)
	3.	Appropriate pricing tier
	4.	Relevant certifications (if you have compliance needs)
Evaluation process:
	1.	Initial calls (30 min each) - Gut check, basic alignment
	2.	Detailed proposals with specific scope and pricing
	3.	Reference checks (minimum 2 per finalist)
	4.	Technical deep dive (demo their tools, meet your engineer)
	5.	Contract review (attorney review if >$50K annual)
	6.	Final decision based on scorecard + gut
Start small:
	âˆ™	6-month initial term if possible (theyâ€™ll want 1+ year)
	âˆ™	Defined pilot scope rather than all-in immediately
	âˆ™	Clear success metrics - What does good look like at 90 days?
